      "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body": "<p><code>Is it possible to construct a snippet of code in java that would make a hypothetical java.lang.ChuckNorrisException uncatchable?</code></p>\n<p>Yes, and here's the answer: Design your <code>java.lang.ChuckNorrisException</code> such that it is not an instance of <code>java.lang.Throwable</code>. Why? An unthrowable object is uncatchable by definition because you can never catch something that can never be thrown.</p>\n"
